http://www.w3schools.com/css/css_background.asp&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Background&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;simple&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;nice&amp;nbsp;=)&lt;br&gt;</questionanswer>
  </question>
  <question id="0_0_1_0_0_2:1" type="2">
    <questiontext>&lt;br&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Css&amp;nbsp;core&amp;nbsp;:&amp;nbsp;gradient&amp;nbsp;as&amp;nbsp;background,&amp;nbsp;describe.&amp;nbsp;Provide&amp;nbsp;examples&amp;nbsp;.&lt;br&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</questiontext>
    <questionanswer>Nice&amp;nbsp;Css&amp;nbsp;gradients&amp;nbsp;generator&amp;nbsp;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;
http://www.colorzilla.com/gradient-editor/&lt;br&gt;
===================================&lt;br&gt;
===================================&lt;br&gt;
Link&amp;nbsp;to&amp;nbsp;w3&lt;br&gt;
http://www.w3schools.com/css/css3_gradients.asp&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
CSS3&amp;nbsp;defines&amp;nbsp;two&amp;nbsp;types&amp;nbsp;of&amp;nbsp;gradients:&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Linear&amp;nbsp;Gradients&amp;nbsp;(goes&amp;nbsp;down/up/left/right/diagonally)&lt;br&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Radial&amp;nbsp;Gradients&amp;nbsp;(defined&amp;nbsp;by&amp;nbsp;their&amp;nbsp;center)&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
The&amp;nbsp;numbers&amp;nbsp;in&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;table&amp;nbsp;specifies&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;first&amp;nbsp;browser&amp;nbsp;version&amp;nbsp;that&amp;nbsp;fully&amp;nbsp;supports&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;property.&lt;br&gt;
Numbers&amp;nbsp;followed&amp;nbsp;by&amp;nbsp;-webkit-,&amp;nbsp;-moz-,&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;-o-&amp;nbsp;specifies&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;first&amp;nbsp;version&amp;nbsp;that&amp;nbsp;worked&amp;nbsp;with&amp;nbsp;a&amp;nbsp;prefix.&lt;br&gt;
=======================================&lt;br&gt;
CSS3&amp;nbsp;Linear&amp;nbsp;Gradients&lt;br&gt;
Syntax&lt;br&gt;
background:&amp;nbsp;linear-gradient(direction,&amp;nbsp;color-stop1,&amp;nbsp;color-stop2,&amp;nbsp;...);&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
------------------------------------------------&lt;br&gt;
CSS3&amp;nbsp;Radial&amp;nbsp;Gradients&lt;br&gt;
Syntax&lt;br&gt;
background:&amp;nbsp;radial-gradient(center,&amp;nbsp;shape&amp;nbsp;size,&amp;nbsp;start-color,&amp;nbsp;...,&amp;nbsp;last-color);&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
----------------------------------------------------------&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Example&amp;nbsp;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;
#grad1&amp;nbsp;{&lt;br&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;height:&amp;nbsp;200px;&lt;br&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;color:&amp;nbsp;black;&lt;br&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;background:&amp;nbsp;linear-gradient(to&amp;nbsp;right,#fff,&amp;nbsp;#ddd);&lt;br&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;
}&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;div&amp;nbsp;id="grad1"&gt;Some&amp;nbsp;text&amp;nbsp;here&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;</questionanswer>
  </question>
